{
  "texts": [
    "Large language Model alignment with human preferences is critical to ensure that the responses of pre-trained LLMs to prompts are consistent with human preferences (Bai et al., 2022; Ouyang et al., 2022; Stiennon et al., 2020).",
    "Recently, Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) (Ouyang et al., 2022; Christiano et al., 2017) has been proposed for fine-tuning language models based on human preferences.",
    "RLHF involves initially fitting a reward signal derived from human preference data with the application of reinforcement learning algorithms, such as Proximal Policy Optimization (Schulman et al., 2017), to optimize language model policy to maximize rewards.",
    "RLHF demonstrates impressive capabilities across diverse tasks.",
    "Yet, the reinforcement learning approach presents significant challenges, such † Work done during internship at Amazon as computational inefficiency and training instability (Engstrom et al., 2020; Rafailov et al., 2024)."
  ]
}